Ques 1. Create a class Circle and use inheritance to create another class cylinder from it.

Program :

class circle{
    int r;

    int getR() {
        return r;
    }
    public void setR(int r) {
        this.r = r;
        System.out.println("This is the radius of circle : "+r);
    }
}
class cylinder extends circle{
    int h;
    public int getH(){
        return h;
    }
    public void setH(int h){
        this.h = h;
        System.out.println("This is height of cylinder : "+h);
    };
}
public class practice {
    public static void main(String[] args){
        circle c = new circle();
        c.setR(4);
        cylinder cy = new cylinder();
        cy.setH(5);
        cy.setR(3);
    }
}

Output :

This is the radius of circle : 4
This is height of cylinder : 5
This is the radius of circle : 3

Process finished with exit code 0


