Ques 5. What is the order of constructor execution for the following inheritance hierarchy.
                  +-------+
                  | Base  |      
                  +-------+
                      |
                  +------------+
                  | Derived 1  |      
                  +------------+
                      |
                  +------------+
                  | Derived 2  |      
                  +------------+

    Derived2 obj = new Derived2();
    Which constructor(s) will be executed & in what order 

Program : 

class base{
    base(){
        System.out.println("Constructor of Base class ");
    }
}
class Derived1 extends base{
    Derived1(){
        System.out.println("Constructor of Derived class 1");
    }
}
class Derived2 extends Derived1{
    Derived2(){
        System.out.println("Constructor of Derived class 2");
    }
}
public class practice{
    public static void main(String[] args){
        Derived2 D = new Derived2();
    }
}

Output :

Constructor of Base class 
Constructor of Derived class 1
Constructor of Derived class 2

Process finished with exit code 0

Thus constructor will be called in order --> Base class --> Derived1 class --> Derived2 class
